title: LICENSE missing from PyPi source archive
body:
Could you add the `LICENSE` file to the source archive uploaded to PyPI with the next release? You probably just need to create a `MANIFEST.in`.

The license you chose (GPL) requires distributing that exact file with every distribution of your code.

Thanks!

title: Add an option to evaluate the coding potential of the reverse strand
body: Currently, RNAsamba only evaluates the transcript sequences that are given as input. But in some cases the user may not know the true orientation of the transcript, so a `--check_reverse_complement` option would be useful.

title: Package the model files in the library
body: Currently, users need to download one of the two model files (or train their own) before executing RNAsamba. Packaging pre-trained models in the library would spare users from downloading external files and make RNAsambe more user-friendly.

title: Release Python 3.9 builds
body: Now that Python 3.9 is out, RNAsamba should have a build for it. We should probably transition the CI to GitHub Actions in the meanwhile.

title: Incompatibility with tensorflow version in rnasamba (1,5-2) and keras (2.2<)
body:
Hello, im trying to use RNAsamba but i have a few issues. Im ussing ubuntu 20.10 (groovy) where the default version of python is 3.8 and tensorflow is 2.3. So i proced to install RNAsamba  but it throws me the following error : 
![Screenshot from 2021-03-13 14-16-31](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/80530322/111038255-c71a6c80-8406-11eb-9d81-6be07ac726c5.png)
So i tried to downgrade the version of my tensorflow but:
![Screenshot from 2021-03-13 14-17-14](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/80530322/111038271-d7cae280-8406-11eb-9e83-a5c2f77410d2.png)
![Screenshot from 2021-03-13 14-17-36](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/80530322/111038284-e1544a80-8406-11eb-9d65-6281b171bb81.png)
So i created a environment with python 3.5 and:
![Screenshot from 2021-03-13 14-21-41](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/80530322/111038419-840cc900-8407-11eb-8e8c-f4a64f158462.png)
then i found out that biopython version 1.76 supports python 3.5 and installed it and finally was able to install RNAsamba. I tried to execute and: 
![Screenshot from 2021-03-13 14-26-48](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/80530322/111038516-32187300-8408-11eb-9294-57ab05a3341d.png)
So i forced the upgrade of tensorflow to v 2.2 with pip install tensorflow==2.2 and in the end gives me this error and when i tried to execute RNAsamba it cant execute because it need tensorflow v 1.5-2:
![Screenshot from 2021-03-13 14-36-09](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/80530322/111038787-87a14f80-8409-11eb-8c4f-238f6827d275.png)
After this is a chain of errors in a circle given the incompatibility between the version of tensorflow that keras occupies and RNAsamba .
Any help on this error is welcome :(
